Registration Details for iSES-2023

  • All the registration fees are inclusive of 18% GST.
  • Each of the Regular/Short/SRF/RDS papers and Posters for the technical program needs to be registered at the respective registration rate as described in Table: I.
  • At least one of the authors must register before 15th November 2023 and present the paper at the symposium for inclusion in the proceedings as per the IEEE regulations.
  • Any registration after 15th November, 2023 will be subject to “On-the-Spot Registration Charges.”
  • All the charges related to the transection of registration fees for foreign authors/delegates will have to be borne by themselves. The net registration fees as per the table:I and II must be deposited to the organizer’s account.

  • iSES-2023 invites all authors and all other interested to attend the Pre-symposium Tutorials, , Keynote addresses, Plenary talks and Symposium sessions. It would provide opportunity to grow network with international peers and attend 100+ high-quality presentations in 4 days.
  • The other authors and non-author delegates are required to register at the Delegate rates as shown in Table: II

Additional Registration Information

  • Regular Registration Fees include a conference kit, breakfast, high tea, lunch, dinner on 19th December, and local sight-seeing.
  • It does not include any other expenses like stay, travel, local transport etc.
  • Indian Student registration in Basic category includes breakfast, high tea, and lunch only.
  • The Pre-symposium Tutorials will be free for all categories of registration. However, candidates interested only in the tutorials have to pay a nominal fee as given in Table: III.

Each participant needs to fill up the Google Form after transferring registration fees.

While filling the form, you are required to enter all the details related to the Bank Transaction, including the transaction ID.
